description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit a Domestic Assistant (cleaner) to join our team at Department of Psychiatry, Kings Drive, Eastbourne, BN21 2UD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you approachable, flexible and willing to work as part of a team? Do you want to help us make a positive difference for the people in our care? If you answered yes, then we have the perfect role for you. Applicants must have good communication and interpersonal skills, be able to undertake varied manual tasks, and have experience of working within the Cleaning Industry or the Catering Industry and with the general public.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for self-motivated individuals who can work equally well on their own or as part of a team, to deliver and achieve high standards of environmental cleaning and prepare meals for service. We need people who recognise the importance of a clean environment and food safety as well as the important of adherence to infection prevention and control standards at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours are Monday to Friday afternoons between 12:00 and 19:30, a total of 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value our workforce and will ensure that you will have the training and support you need to achieve the highest standards possible. If you feel that you can make a positive contribution to our team and work to our exacting standards we welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Michel Brown&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Facilities Manager - East&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Michel.Brown@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0300 304 0723&lt;/p&gt;
